considering how much has happened this year it truly felt like it came and left so quickly. this year was really weird. so i decided to reflect on the things that i think affected me the most. instead of dwell on them, shed some light where the was darkness.
you never know who might need to hear some words of wisdom and you know what they say, if this can help at least one other person feeling what i’ve felt…. well then that sure is something special.

✨feeling enough: reminder to myself and anyone else who might be feeling this way, you are ALWAYS enough. more than you know. you don’t get to feel the perceptions or reactions of others but for all you know, you are somebody else’s reason for being inspired, being confident, or simply just to keep going.

✨self love: i realized that it doesn’t have to be a lifelong battle. if there are so many other people who love me despite all my flaws (and trust me i’m far from perfect), why can’t i allow myself to feel that same love? why be someone i’m not when in reality nobody fucking cares. just be you. be your most authentic self and love that person like your life depends on it, because it does.

✨letting go: this was probably one of the hardest things i struggled with this year. leaving people and friendships behind because i know that it’s for the best. knowing damn well a person does not deserve my friendship and kindness anymore. the feeling of being so used, it really really got to me. reality is, people change and it’s just a part of life and i get to choose to move on from them. the other loss of dear friend that i grew up with, it isn’t the same. the grief of never getting to see a friend again is never ending. the only thing i can say to ease that pain, is that grief is really just love. love for a person who is no longer with us and that in itself is a beautiful thing.

✨finding myself: coming to the realization that this is only one small chapter in a much larger story helps me keep things in perspective. knowing that finding myself is not something that’s going to happen overnight, it’s a lifelong event and i need to enjoy it while it lasts.

did you know the uk bans over 1300 chemicals from cosmetics and beauty products like shampoo, conditioner, face wash, etc. while the United States only bans 11. 🤯 #scary! drug store products are notorious for having crazy ingredients like silicones, sulfates, parabens, even butane and propane in them. although drugstore shampoos do contain high-grade ingredients found in salon products, they only contain small amounts of them. they typically contain chemicals, which can strip your hair of its natural oils, essentially drying it out. they’re also known for diluting their products with fillers. these tend to make your hair feel super soft, but can also leave behind a waxy build-up. basically, your hair feels soft but isn’t actually hydrated from within.

this one has sat in my drafts for a while but here goes nothing. the first 4 photos were from 2018. i was extremely anxious, unhappy, drinking and living a terribly unhealthy lifestyle to numb myself of pain i was feeling and things i was going through. i was with someone who was controlling, narcissistic, and abusive. i was severely underweight and thought nothing was wrong when someone told me they were worried about me. i have always had a positive body image… but i look back at these photos and can’t believe what i see. i think “no wonder people were worried about me”. 

thankfully, i don’t recognize that girl anymore. i look at those photos and think “who is she?”. all it does is make me so sad for her, that she didn’t see a way out of it all. that time in my life felt like a fever dream. it didn’t really feel like it was real life. my gears were stuck in neutral and i was okay with that.

until i wasn’t ok, because i was not okay with settling for the bare minimum. not okay with hating myself and not treating my body with the respect it deserves. not okay with blacking out and not remembering what happened the night before because i wanted to feel numb but then constantly having to put all the pieces back together. i was not okay with feeling broken anymore. 

so i decided to make a change.

i started cutting out the people in my life who weren’t healthy for me (still do sometimes lol). i started a business that completely transformed my life, my outlook on what’s possible for me to achieve, and my entire outlook on self love and confidence. i started prioritizing my family and the friends who lift me up not bring me down. i started choosing ME! And god damn i am not about to tell you all this was easy but what it did feel was SO DAMN GOOD. I still stifle with anxiety and depression but manage it with my psychiatrist and therapist. everyday i am finding myself again and it feels great. 

who is she? she is free, she is healthy, she is happy, and she still may be a work in progress, but she is so proud of how far she has come. 

whatever your going through, you are not alone. my dms are always open. 🫶🏽

It’s absolutely bittersweet for me to announce that I will no longer be promoting for Monat. 

The past five years have taught me so much. Everything I know about the industry I owe to the company and many mentors who have poured themselves into me over the years. I’m so immensely grateful for the experience, but as I grow into the person I am meant to be, I’ve realized it no longer aligns with the things I want from life.

I know I’ve kept everyone in suspense about where my new journey starts and I’m excited to announce I will be partnering with Le-Vel! @le_velofficial 

A year ago I had tried quite a few different products behind the scenes. I tried products from every company in the industry and the only one that always stuck out with me was Le-Vel. It wasn’t just about loving the products but about getting to see the leadership training in the community.

So when it come down to where I wanted to go, my choice was easy. Yes, these rank match and bonuses are great! 😮‍💨 but at the end of the day I’m truly here for the products, people, and community this company has built. 

I want to end the stigma on social selling and show people what you can really do when you have the right support system and someone who believes in you.

If that something you want to be a part of then message me because we’re about to do big things here!!!

i bought this shirt a year ago but two nights ago was the first time that i felt confident enough to wear it. i think that sometimes we get so comfortable or complacent that we wake up one day and realize WTH have i done?! maybe more so- WTH haven’t i done to keep myself healthy?

for me, that wake up call was last year after the holidays. my confidence wasn’t just in the trash it was a dumpster fire. not that a number on a scale is what matters, but i had never weighed so much in my life. i barely recognized myself in the mirror and i needed change. at that point it was getting myself back into a healthy routine, learning about better habits and figuring out what foods were best for MY body (because every body is different). 

i really don’t know what this journey would have looked like without Thrive. i have been looking at pictures from last year side by side to the ones we took this year and the difference is just amazing. not only do i look better but i FEEL better. 🥹

as someone who struggles with mental health issues, this was not an easy feat. the beginning of any journey can feel rocky but i had no idea that adding 3 simple steps to my daily routine could change my life and outlook on life so much. this system is AMAZING and tailor made to help you achieve whatever your health goals are 🫶🏽
